Eternal Egypt : masterworks of ancient art from the British Museum

University of California | 2001 | Pdf | Eng | 292 pag | ISBN10 0520230868 | 87.2 MB

Eternal Egypt: Masterworks of Ancient Art from the British Museum is one of the greatest loan exhibitions ever to have been mounted from the collections of the British Museum. Designed to illustrate the development and achievements of ancient Egyptian art over a period of three thousand years and more, it consists of 144 representative works of diverse type, including sculpture, relief, papyri, ostraca, jewelry, cosmetic objects, and items of funerary equipment. Almost all have been drawn from the Museum's permanent exhibitions, many are among the finest examples of their kind to have survived from antiquity
